<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="context/main_template/macros/master"
      i18n:domain="emas.mobiletheme">
<body>

<metal:content-core fill-slot="main">

    <tal:no_active_services condition="not:view/services_active">
        <h3>You don't have access to Intelligent Practice right now</h3>

        <p>Why?</p>

        <p>When your account was created you either:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>paid for subscribtion and your subscription has expired, or</li>
            <li>you automatically had access via our time-limited, free trial and that has expired.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>What can you do about this?</p>

        <p>You need to <a href="#" tal:attributes="href string:${context/absolute_url}/@@order">subscribe to Intelligent Practice</a>. 
            If your school signed you up then you should ask your 
            teacher what the status of the school's subscription is. 
            If you signed up individually you need to renew your 
            subscription via the <a href="#" tal:attributes="href string:${context/absolute_url}/@@order">orders page</a>.</p>

        <p>Even if your school signed you up originally, you can make an 
            individual order to extend your account.</p>

        <p>What about my previous data?</p>

        <p>We don't delete your Intelligent Practice history for 3 months. As 
        long as you subscribe again within 3 months your history will still be 
        available and Intelligent Practice will be able to use that 
        information to give you better advice.</p>
    </tal:no_active_services>

    <tal:services_active condition="view/services_active">
        <tal:update tal:condition="view/update"/>

        <tal:question tal:condition="view/question">
            <div id="practice-mini-dashboard">
                <div id="mini-dashboard-question-count">Questions completed: <strong tal:content="view/questionscompleted">1</strong></div>
                <div id="mini-dashboard-points-scored">Points: <strong tal:content="view/pointsscored">1</strong> / <strong tal:content="view/pointstotal">3</strong></div>
            </div>
        </tal:question>


        <tal:rewriteimg define="html view/html;
                                helper nocall:context/@@mobile_image_mathml_rewriter;
                                html python:helper.processHTML(html);">
        
            <tal:dashboard tal:condition="view/dashboard">
                <h1 id="parent-fieldname-title">Practice Home</h1>

                <h3 id="booktitle" tal:content="view/booktitle">Maths Grade 10</h3>

                <ul>
                    <li tal:repeat="section view/sections">
                        <span class="dashboard-section-title-1"><a href="#" title="Click to practise Algebraic expressions" tal:attributes="href section/href; title section/alttitle" tal:content="section/title">Algebraic expressions</a></span>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </tal:dashboard>

            <tal:question tal:condition="view/question">
                <div id="howtowrite" tal:condition="view/howtowrite">
                    <h2>How should I type my answer?</h2>
                    <div tal:content="structure view/howtowrite"/>
                </div>
                <div id="links">
                    <a href="#" class="dashboard" tal:attributes="href view/dashboard_url">
                        Return to practice home
                    </a> 
                    <a href="#" class="problem" tal:attributes="href view/reportproblem_url">
                        Report a problem
                    </a>
                </div>
                <div tal:replace="structure html" />
            </tal:question>
        </tal:rewriteimg>
    </tal:services_active>

</metal:content-core>
            
</body>
</html> 
